nce 1991 as the ''UNCAF Nations Cup'' and serves as a qualifying event for the [[CONCACAF Gold Cup]]. The competition was re-branded as the ''Copa Centroamericana'' from the 2011 edition. El Salvador has participated in all of the tournaments and has managed to get up to third place in various occasions.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=10|[[Copa Centroamericana]] record \n|-\n!Year\n!Round\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}*\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon;\"\n| {{flagicon|Costa Rica}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 1991|1991]]||Fourth place||3||0||1||2||2||9\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon;\"\n| {{flagicon|Honduras}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 1993|1993]]||Fourth place||3||0||1||2||1||5\n|- style=\"background:#c96;\"\n|style=\"border: 3px solid red\"|{{flagicon|El Salvador}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 1995|1995]]||Third place||4||2||0||2||5||5\n|- style=\"background:#c96;\"\n| {{flagicon|Guatemala}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 1997|1997]]||Third place||5||3||1||1||5||5\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon;\"\n| {{flagicon|Costa Rica}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 1999|1999]]||Fourth place||5||1||1||3||3||9\n|- style=\"background:#c96;\"\n| {{flagicon|Honduras}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 2001|2001]]||Third place||6||2||4||0||8||4\n|- style=\"background:#c96;\"\n| {{flagicon|Panama}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 2003|2003]]||Third place||5||3||0||2||6||4\n|-\n| {{flagicon|Guatemala}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 2005|2005]]||Group stage||2||0||0||2||1||3\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon;\"\n|style=\"border: 3px solid red\"|{{flagicon|El Salvador}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 2007|2007]]||Fourth place||5||2||1||2||4||5\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon;\"\n| {{flagicon|Honduras}} [[UNCAF Nations Cup 2009|2009]]||Fourth place||5||1||1||3||5||6\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon;\"\n| {{flagicon|Panama}} [[2011 Copa Centroamericana|2011]]||Fourth place||5||2||1||2||7||6\n|- style