rty wars]]\n[[Category:Guerrilla wars]]\n[[Category:History of Belfast]]\n[[Category:History of Northern Ireland]]\n[[Category:Politics of Northern Ireland]]\n[[Category:Wars involving Ireland]]\n[[Category:Wars involving the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|Troubles}}\n{{short description|1960s\u20131998 ethnopolitical conflict in Northern Ireland}}\n{{EngvarB|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict    = The Troubles\n| partof      = \n| image       = [[File:Map of Ireland's capitals.png|225px|alt=a map showing the outline of Ireland in the colour green with the capitals of the North and South marked on it]]\n| caption     = Political map of Ireland\n| date        = Late 1960s\u20131998<ref>{{cite web |last1=Melaugh |first1=Martin |title=Frequently Asked Questions \u2013 The Northern Ireland Conflict |url=https://cain.ulster.ac.uk/faq/faq2.htm |work=[[Conflict Archive on the Internet]]|publisher= [[Ulster University]]  |accessdate=18 May 2017 |date=3 February 2006}}</ref><ref name=\"aughey7\">{{cite book | last=Aughey | first=Arthur | title=The Politics of Northern Ireland: Beyond the Belfast Agreement | publisher=Routledge | location=London New York | year=2005 | isbn=978-0-415-32788-6 | oclc=55962335 | page=7}}</ref><ref name=\"Ireland 1999, page 221\">{{cite book |last1=Holland |first1=Jack |title=Hope Against History: The Course of Conflict in Northern Ireland |date=August 1999 |publisher=[[Henry Holt and Company]] |isbn=9780805060874 |page=[https://archive.org/details/hopeagainsthisto00holl/page/221 221] |quote=The troubles were over, but the killing continued. Some of the heirs to Ireland's violent traditions refused to give up their inheritance. |url=https://archive.org/details/hopeagainsthisto00holl/page/221 }}</ref><ref name=\"Northern Ireland Conflict' page 250\">{{cite book |last1=Gillespie |first1=Gordon |title=Historical Dictionary of the Norther