e |first1=Lisa Riley |title=Gubernatorial candidate Greg Hughes names southern Utah commissioner as running mate |url=https://www.deseret.com/utah/2020/4/14/21220814/gubernatorial-candidate-greg-hughes-names-southern-utah-commissioner-as-running-mate |website=Deseret News |language=en |date=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Jon Huntsman Jr.]], former [[United States Ambassador to Russia]], [[United States Ambassador to China|China]] and [[United States Ambassador to Singapore|Singapore]], and former Governor of Utah<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rodgers |first1=Bethany |title=Jon Huntsman to launch his 2020 run for Utah governor |url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2019/11/14/jon-huntsman-launch-his/ |website=The Salt Lake Tribune |date=November 13, 2019}}</ref>\n**[[Michelle Kaufusi]], mayor of [[Provo, Utah|Provo]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Stevens |first1=Taylor |last2=Wood |first2=Benjamin |title=Jon Huntsman names Provo Mayor Michelle Kaufusi as running mate in 2020 governor\u2019s race |url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2020/02/07/jon-huntsman-names-provo/ |website=The Salt Lake Tribune |date=February 8, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Aimee Winder Newton]], [[Salt Lake County]] councilwoman<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Donoghue |first1=Amy Joi |title=Aimee Winder Newton announces 2020 run for Utah governor |url=https://www.deseret.com/utah/2019/10/23/20928401/aimee-winder-newton-2020-run-utah-governor |website=Deseret News |accessdate=October 24, 2019 |date=October 23, 2019}}</ref>\n**[[John Dougall (Utah politician)|John Dougall]], Utah State Auditor<ref>{{cite web |last=Klopfensten |first=Jacob |title=Utah State Auditor John Dougall will be Aimee Winder Newton\u2019s running mate in Utah governor campaign |url=https://www.ksl.com/article/46733962/utah-state-auditor-john-dougall-will-be-aimee-winder-newtons-running-mate-in-utah-governor-campaign |website=KSL.com |accessdate=March 25, 2020 |date=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Thomas Wright (Utah politician)|Thomas Wright]], Republican National Committee executive committee member and former chair of the [[Utah Republican Party]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wood |first1=Benjamin |title=Former Utah GOP Chairman Thomas Wright is running for governor. Greg Hughes to announce bid next week. |url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2020/01/02/former-utah-gop-chairman/ |website=The Salt Lake Tribune |accessdate=January 3, 2020 |date=January 2, 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Rob Bishop]], U.S. Representative for [[Utah's 1st congressional district]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Wood |first1=Benjamin |title=Congressman Rob Bishop will be Thomas Wright\u2019s running mate in 2020 governor\u2019s race |url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2020/01/16/congressman-rob-bishop/ |website=The Salt Lake Tribune |date=January 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Thomas Wright adds US Rep. Rob Bishop to his governor ticket |url=https://www.cachevalleydaily.com/news/archive/2020/01/17/thomas-wright-adds-us-rep-rob-bishop-to-his-governor-ticket/#.XkGk_EdKiUk |website=Cache Valley Daily |publisher=Associated Press |date=January 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====Declined====\n*[[Rob Bishop]], U.S. Representative (endorsed Wright, who in turn chose Bishop to run with him as his lieutenant governor)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehill.com/policy/energy-environment/477978-top-natural-resources-republican-says-he-wont-run-for-utah-governor|title=Top Natural Resources Republican won't run for Utah governor|first=Rachel|last=Frazin|date=January 13, 2020|website=TheHill}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://utahpolicy.com/index.php/features/today-at-utah-policy/16376-bishop-reportedly-testing-the-water-for-a-possible-gubernatorial-run-in-2020|title=Bishop reportedly testing the water for a possible gubernatorial run in 2020|work=UtahPolicy.com|first=Bob|last=Bernick|date=April 12, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2018/10/28/latest-poll-potential/|title=Latest poll of potential Utah Republican candidates for 2020 gove