 governor in 2020|url=https://utahpolicy.com/index.php/features/today-at-utah-policy/18961-utah-republicans-believe-sen-mike-lee-may-be-preparing-to-run-for-governor-in-2020|publisher=Utah Policy|date=January 6, 2019|accessdate=January 7, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailykos.com/story/2019/1/7/1824229/-Ultra-conservative-Utah-senator-picks-social-media-fight-that-might-signal-a-bid-for-governor|title=Ultra-conservative Utah senator picks social media fight that might signal a bid for governor|website=Daily Kos|access-date=2019-01-07}}</ref>\n*[[Gail Miller (businesswoman)|Gail Miller]], owner of the [[Utah Jazz]]<ref name=\":4\" />\n*Greg Miller, former CEO of the Utah Jazz<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n*[[Sean Reyes]], Attorney General of Utah<ref>{{cite web |last1=Winslow |first1=Ben |title=Utah Attorney General Sean Reyes won\u2019t run for governor, but will seek re-election |url=https://fox13now.com/2020/01/18/utah-attorney-general-sean-reyes-wont-run-for-governor-but-will-seek-re-election/ |website=FOX 13 |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |date=January 18, 2020}}</ref>\n*Josh Romney, real estate developer and son of [[Mitt Romney]]<ref name=\":4\" /><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865676494/Ann-Romney-sees-son-Josh-Romney-running-for-Utah-governor.html|title=Ann Romney sees son Josh Romney running for Utah governor|last=Romboy|first=Dennis|date=2017-03-27|website=DeseretNews.com|language=en|access-date=2018-12-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865644819/Josh-Romney-strongly-considering-run-for-governor-in-2020.html|title=Josh Romney 'strongly considering' run for governor in 2020|first=Lisa Riley|last=Roche|date=4 January 2016|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n===Endorsements===\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Spencer Cox \n| list =\n; Governors\n* [[Gary Herbert]], Utah<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2019/05/14/lt-gov-spencer-cox/|title=Lt. Gov. Spencer Cox announces he is running for Utah governor, vows a \u2018different,\u2019 positive campaign|work=[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]|date=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n; Local officials\n* 125 mayors of Utah<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heraldextra.com/sanpete-county/news/utah-mayors-endorse-spencer-cox-as-utah-s-next-governor/article_8d4769f6-2775-5936-9960-13b3c8f43861.html|title=125 Utah mayors endorse Spencer Cox as Utah\u2019s next governor|work=[[Daily Herald]]: Sanpete County edition|date=November 21, 2019|accessdate=February 24, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Jon Huntsman Jr.\n| list =\n; Notable individuals\n* [[Abby Huntsman]], journalist and television personality (daughter of Jon Huntsman Jr.)<ref>{{Cite tweet|url= https://twitter.com/huntsmanabby/status/1195001322711457792?s=21 |title= It\u2019s official!! Let\u2019s do this Utah |last= Huntsman |first=Abby|date=November 14, 2019|user=HuntsmanAbby|access-date=November 18, 2019|number= 1195001322711457792 }}</ref>\n* [[Meghan McCain]], columnist, author, political commentator, and daughter of [[John McCain]]<ref>{{Cite tweet|url=https://twitter.com/meghanmccain/status/1195757122904088576?s=21 |title= Late to this tweet but forgive me, I\u2019m in London. Congratulations to the entire Huntsman family and looking forward to @JonHuntsman\u2019s return to Utah governorship! \ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8 |last=McCain|first=Meghan|date=November 16, 2019|user=MeghanMcCain|access-date=November 18, 2019|number= 1195757122904088576 }}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Thomas Wright\n| list = \n; U.S. Representatives\n* [[Rob Bishop]], U.S. Representative from [[Utah's 1st congressional district|UT-1]] since 2003<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2020/01/13/rep-rob-bishop-says-he/|title=Rob Bishop says he will not run for governor; endorses Thomas Wright|work=[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]|last=Davidson|first=Lee|date=January 13, 2020|accessdate=January 13, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign=bottom\n! Poll source\n! Date(s)<br>administered\n! Sample<br>size\n! Margin<br>of error\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Jeff<br>Burningham\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Spencer<br>Cox\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Jan<br>Garbett\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Greg<br>Hughes\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Jon<br>Huntsman Jr.\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Aimee<br>Winder Newton\n! style=\"width:40px;\"| Thomas<br>Wright\n! Other\n! Undecided\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [https://utahpolicy.com/index.php/features/today-at-utah-policy/23528-poll-shows-gop-nomination-for-governor-turning-into-a-three-person-race-between-cox-huntsman-and-hughes Y2 Analytics]\n| March 23-30, 2020\n| 641\n|\u00b1&nbsp;3.9%\n| 5%\n|{{party shading/Republican}} | '''40%'''\n| < 1%\n| 16%\n| 33%\n| 4%\n| 1%\n|<1%{{efn|Jason Christensen with <1%}}\n| \u2014\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [https://www.deseret.com/utah/2020/4/1/21201407/poll-jon-huntsman-spencer-cox-governor-republican-primary-election-undecided-voters-coronavirus Hinckley Institute]\n|March 23\u201328, 2020\n|265\n|\u00b1&nbsp;5.4%\n|7%\n|24%\n|1%\n|7%\n|{{party shading/Republican}} | '''26%'''\n|2%\n|2%\n|\u2013\n| {{party shading/Undecided}} | '''32%'''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [https://utahpolicy.com/index.php/features/today-at-utah-policy/23403-poll-shows-huntsman-tied-with-cox-in-race-for-gop-nomination Dan Jones & Associates/Salt<br>Lake Chamber of Commerce]\n|February 28 \u2013 March 11, 2020\n|338 (V)\n|\u00b1&nbsp;5.3%\n|6%\n|{{party shading/Republican}} | '''30%'''\n|2%\n|12%\n|27%\n|4%\n|6%\n|\u2013\n|15%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [https://www.deseret.com/utah/2020/3/6/21168084/jon-huntsman-spencer-cox-governor-poll-deseret-news-hinckley-institute-politics-republican/ Hinckley Institute]\n|February 24 \u2013 March 1, 2020\n|312\n|\u00b1&nbsp;5.5