olitician)|Thomas Wright]]\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.00%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Democratic primary==\n===Candidates===\n====Declared====\n*[[Neil Hansen]], former state representative<ref name=\"UTGOVC\"/>\n*Ryan Jackson<ref name=\"UTGOVC\"/>\n*Zachary Moses, CEO of HeTravel.com<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2019/07/19/zachary-moses-democratic/|title=Zachary Moses, a Democratic candidate for governor, wants to break up Republican control of Utah and build a space port|date=July 19, 2019|first=Benjamin|last=Wood|work=[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]|accessdate=July 23, 2019}}</ref>\n*Christopher Peterson, [[University of Utah]] law professor and former [[Consumer Financial Protection Bureau|CFPB]] official<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tanner |first1=Courtney |title=University of Utah professor launches bid to become Utah\u2019s next governor |url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2020/03/05/university-utah-professor/ |accessdate=March 5, 2020 |work=The Salt Lake Tribune |date=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n*Nikki Pino, youth counselor<ref name=UT2020>{{Cite web|url=https://elections.utah.gov/2020-signature-gathering-candidates#Federal|title=2020 Signature Gathering Candidates - Lieutenant Governor's Office: Elections|website=elections.utah.gov}}</ref>\n*Archie Williams III<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://voteinfo.utah.gov/wp-content/uploads/sites/42/2020/03/2020-DoC-Archie-A-Williams-III_Redacted.pdf|title=2020 Qualified Political Party State Constitutional Office Declaration of Candidacy - Archie A. Williams, III|last=|first=|date=March 20, 2020|website=Utah Secretary of State|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====Declined====\n*[[Peter Corroon]], former [[Utah Democratic Party]] chair, former mayor of [[Salt Lake County, Utah|Salt Lake County]], and nominee for governor in [[2010 Utah gubernator